{"by": "zimpenfish", "id": 43181996, "kids": [43185545], "parent": 43179304, "text": "I remember, a long time ago, having to try and parse text out from RTF documents and I would rather have every internal organ pecked out by sparrows than try and deal with that abomination again.<p>&gt; still text-based<p>The point about Markdown is that you don&#x27;t need a complex parser[0] to be able to interpret the files - a simple human can read a Markdown file and get the gist of what is going on.  RTF has a whole mess of control strings and codes going on that get in the way of a simple visual understanding.<p>&gt; I can&#x27;t express simple formatting such as &quot;make this text red&quot; in Markdown.<p>You can add raw HTML to Markdown which would accomplish this (at the expense of moving away from the &quot;simple plain text&quot;, obvs.)  There&#x27;s a bunch of Markdown parsers with extensions for this kind of thing though (from what I can see, they&#x27;re all not entirely &quot;simple&quot; either which is a shame.)", "time": 1740559944, "type": "comment"}